) below the fall value with minimum amplitude. In practice, fall detection systems are expected to detect all falls, while keeping the false positive rate as low as possible. Results of Table 7 presented poor results in all features. Note how a not too large increment in sensitivity caused significant reductions in specificity. This fact is noteworthy, as most works focus on maximizing accuracy instead of favoring fall detection. Authors that addressed this issue usually included a false-alarm button as part of their methodology [29].
